StudyInfo.StudyNameEntrez: Admixture mapping for Breast Cancer in Latinas

Policy.acknowledgement_statement: Data were provided via dbGaP project phs000912.v1.p1. Study investigators include Elad Ziv and Esther M. John. Genotyping for this study was supported by a grant from NIH (R01 CA120120 to E. Ziv). Sample collection was supported in part by Department of Defense Breast Cancer Research Program (BC030551 to E. Ziv). Additional support was provided by NIH (K24CA169004). The SFBCS was supported by grants to E. John from NIH (R01 CA063446 and R01 CA077305), Department of Defense Breast Cancer Research Program (DAMD17-96-1-6071), and the California Breast Cancer Research Program (7PB-0068). The Northern California site of the Breast Cancer Family Registry (BCFR) was supported by NIH (U01 CA069417 and UM1 CA164920).

GSR_Access.gsr_mode_label: Unrestricted access (institution responded that the study is not sensitive without submitting a new Institutional Certification)

ConsentGroup.title: Exchange Area
ConsentGroup.name: EA
ConsentGroup.Use-Restriction: Pre-release exchange area for use by study investigators only.

ConsentGroup.title: Disease-Specific (Cancer, benign neoplasms, or hematopoietic diseases related to cancer, MDS)
ConsentGroup.name: DS-CABNHD-MDS
ConsentGroup.Use-Restriction:
Use of the data must be related to Cancer, benign neoplasms, or hematopoietic diseases related to cancer. Use of the data includes methods development research (e.g., development of software or algorithms).
Appendix: Benign neoplasms and hematopoietic diseases are understood as having a potential for significant morbidity in themselves, such as benign brain tumors, neuroendocrine tumors, desmoid tumors, myelodysplastic syndromes, which are reportable or potentially reportable to cancer registries.

ConsentGroup.title: General Research Use (COL)
ConsentGroup.name: GRU-COL
ConsentGroup.Use-Restriction:
Use of the data is limited only by the terms of the model Data Use Certification. Requestor must provide a letter of collaboration with the primary study investigator(s).
Appendix: The letter of collaboration for this study is a "Data Request for Collaborative Analysis" form from the SFBCS. A blank copy can be found at the end of the dataset's Data Use Certification Agreement (see dbGaP study page). Requestor must provide this signed form documenting SFBCS approval. Approval can be obtained by contacting Dr. Esther M. John at esther.john@cpic.org.
